		<div id="landing">
			<h1>Brandon Storz</h1>
            <p>is a <em class="christ">Christian</em> <a href="#" title="I build the backends for websites and web applications."><em>web developer</em></a> who loves good <a href="#" title="As such, I often take on designing roles on websites and applications, as well."><em>design</em></a>. He enjoys <a href="#" title="This website, for instance, is a bit of an extreme case." class="extra-text"><em>minimalism</em> and <em>simplicity</em></a> and integrates them into his everyday work. He believes that the future is in the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cloud_computing" title="Cloud computing is Internet-based computing, whereby software and information are provided on-demand.  These big and fancy words are brought to you by Wikipedia."><em>cloud</em></a> and as such primarily develops <a href="#" title="Or Web Applications. However, you prefer it."><em>web apps</em></a> in his preferred languages, <a href="http://python.org" title="Using 4-space tabs, I might add."><em>Python</em></a> and <a href="http://www.php.net" title="It gets a little messy sometimes, but thats the nature of the beast."><em>PHP</em></a>.  Though he specializes in web applications, he has experience in database administration and systems programming among <a href="#" title="I know PHP, Python, C, C++, C#, Objective-C, Java, Javascript, HTML, and CSS.  I have game development experience with Unity3D, can work with hardware over serial, am confortable in Photoshop, and am even A+ certified."><em>other things</em></a>.  In all of his work, he tries to meld both <a title="You should never have one without the other." href="#"><em>power and ease of use</em></a>.  He has a Bachelor of Science Degree in Computer Science from the <a href="http://utk.edu" title="Go Vols!" class="bigorange"><em>University of Tennessee</em></a>.</p>
            <p class="contact">His friends can contact him on <a href="http://www.facebook.com/bstorz" title="Everyone needs a little facetime, right? (Please excuse the very bad pun)"><em>Facebook</em></a>, and everyone else can send him an <a href="mailto:website@brandonstorz.com" title="I'll get back to you as soon as possible."><em>email</em></a>. Oh, and if you were looking for a less resume-ish site talking about God's glory and/or my love for movies, books, and gaming, then check out <a href="#" title="Stop being lazy.  Click the other Facebook link.  Its even bolded!">Facebook</a>.</p>
            <p id="sdg"><a href="#" class="flip" title='Soli Deo gloria is an old Latin phrase that means "to the glory of God alone."  I seek to do all things to Gods glory, and I pray that my work is of a quality that brings glory to Him.'><em>Soli Deo Gloria</em></a></p>
